# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in real values for local dev.
# DO NOT commit .env.local — it is gitignored, and any VITE_-prefixed value in
# it is exposed to the client at build time, so treat IDs like GTM/GA4/Pixel as
# semi-public but treat any future server-only secrets as sensitive.
# Production values go in your hosting provider's env config (Netlify/Vercel/Cloudflare).
#
# mukyala-the-spa env vars (chunk: spa-tracking-and-consent-2026-05-09).
#
# All four entries below are OPTIONAL. The site builds, runs, and ships with a
# clean network profile when every one of them is unset — that is the design.
#
# Zero-network discipline:
#   - When VITE_GTM_ID is unset, the GTM container snippet is NOT injected
#     into index.html (build-time gate; see scripts/vite-plugin-gtm.mjs).
#     There is no placeholder ID, no console warning, no fetch — even in dev.
#   - When VITE_NEWSLETTER_ENDPOINT is unset, the NewsletterSignup form still
#     renders so layout is QA-able, but submit short-circuits to the success
#     state without POSTing anywhere. (See src/components/NewsletterSignup.tsx
#     for the exact wiring once the implementer pass lands.)
#
# Operator wiring path:
#   1. Create the GTM container in tagmanager.google.com -> set VITE_GTM_ID below.
#   2. Inside the GTM workspace, add tags for GA4 (using VITE_GA4_ID) and the
#      Meta Pixel (using VITE_META_PIXEL_ID). The IDs below are NOT read from
#      the SPA at runtime — they live in this file purely for documentation /
#      onboarding. Code-side, GA4 + Pixel are managed in GTM, not in env vars.
#   3. Pick an email provider (Klaviyo or Mailchimp) and set
#      VITE_NEWSLETTER_ENDPOINT to its embedded-form action URL or a
#      serverless-function proxy that forwards to it.

# Google Tag Manager container ID (e.g. GTM-XXXXXXX). Leave blank to disable
# all third-party tracking.
VITE_GTM_ID=

# Newsletter form POST endpoint. Examples:
#   Klaviyo:  https://manage.kmail-lists.com/subscriptions/subscribe (set list ID inside the form)
#   Mailchimp: https://<region>.list-manage.com/subscribe/post-json?u=<u>&id=<id>
#   Custom:   https://api.mukyala.com/v1/newsletter (serverless proxy)
# Leave blank to disable form submission (form will render but POST will not fire).
VITE_NEWSLETTER_ENDPOINT=

# OPTIONAL — DOCUMENTATION ONLY. Not read by the SPA at runtime. GA4 + Meta
# Pixel are configured INSIDE the GTM workspace (Tags -> New -> GA4 / Pixel).
# Recorded here so onboarding has a single source of truth for the IDs.
# VITE_GA4_ID=
# VITE_META_PIXEL_ID=
